tip.text: Super love this frills-free places for reasonable priced baked goods. Big array of cakes, choccies and morning brekkie pastries such as mini croissants stuffed with cheeses or chocolate. All good!
Daily specials worth a try though the inventive menus on those boards tend to be a hit or miss at times. Still a cosy place conducive to lounge and linger for long brunches, tea, and dinners.

Probably the best place to hit up for (Phu Quoc) seafood in the city. Good place to chill: waterfront dining with sunset views. They are expanding to the next door area with a Bali-centric feel to it.

formattedAddress: 74 Hai Ba Trung St., Ben Nghe Ward, Dist. 1

tip.text: Not a conducive place to stop in for long; more like a pit stop for shoppers in the outlet building. Food is expensive and basic.
Contemporary tapas with a view. Some innovative creations on the menu. Suckling pig, beef cheek, Spanish omelette, scallop carpaccio are some definite orders. Great place for a date.
Always a queue of people to get in and up.

location.address: Bereketzade Mah. Büyük Hendek Cad. Galata
formattedAddress: Bereketzade Mah. Büyük Hendek Cad. Galata

tip.text: Crazy busy promenade in which you can get a fish sandwich from one of the bobbing boats there and share a low table with other locals to enjoy the passing crowds and waterfront sunset views.
Seafood, service and dessert. Waiter was objective and made great suggestions. He recommended a half-portion dessert of each of his personal favourites seeing that I'm on my own.
Chocolate croissant is to die for: melted chocolate swirls on the inside and the entire croissant is drowned in gooey chocolatey goodness on the outside. Not overly sweet. Place is so underrated!
Lively atmosphere; always packed with crowds of people. Reservation recommended. There is no menu here: pick your seafood as you see them, and put in the order for how you want them prepared.

tip.text: Good standard central Vietnamese cuisine. Reasonable prices for the portions. This place is popular with even the locals who originate from central Vietnam, so it must be authentic.
Breakfast rolls are made fresh. Olive rolls are super delish! Contents of bread basket can requested based on preference. Had them bring simit instead of plain rolls to go with other breakfast meals.
